2. Use AppBar Widget in Flutter App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

The AppBar widget in Flutter is used to create a top navigation bar in an application.
It is a part of the Scaffold widget and provides features like:

Title display
Navigation icons (leading)
Action buttons (right side)

It helps in giving structure and navigation to the app.

// main code


import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: AppBarExample(),
    );
  }
}

class AppBarExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("My AppBar"),
        leading: Icon(Icons.menu),
        actions: [
          IconButton(
            icon: Icon(Icons.search),
            onPressed: () {
              print("Search clicked");
            },
          ),
          IconButton(
            icon: Icon(Icons.more_vert),
            onPressed: () {
              print("More options");
            },
          ),
        ],
        backgroundColor: Colors.blue,
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: Text("AppBar Example"),
      ),
    );
  }
}